ferent computers by different people, it is a good idea to have your own repository of reference data versions.","entityUuid":"4c7cd15f-90f9-4ab3-8082-38da4f642de1","questionType":"OptionsQuestion","eventType":"AddQuestionEvent","title":"Will you use a central repository for reference data used in your project?","requiredPhaseUuid":"1796fa3c-9f53-475f-89ff-c66a0453c42e","tagUuids":[],"uuid":"a76b39eb-65e1-4b3a-93a4-550475cfbfd6","parentUuid":"12a85bf3-1407-4783-9e73-564d75e7c98a"},{"annotations":[],"createdAt":"2018-10-01T00:00:00Z","entityUuid":"2efb44c3-7623-464c-807d-809ef666cc53","eventType":"AddReferenceEvent","uuid":"e3710a58-015c-40fb-b02c-fea82c3982c9","parentUuid":"4c7cd15f-90f9-4ab3-8082-38da4f642de1","shortUuid":"pzq","referenceType":"ResourcePageReference"},{"advice":null,"annotations":[],"createdAt":"2018-10-01T00:00:00Z","entityUuid":"67ba0ead-d482-48c8-965a-2472a99648f3","eventType":"AddAnswerEvent","label":"No","uuid":"07404e41-d6db-4c4f-99ec-8a0c458a30ff","parentUuid":"4c7cd15f-90f9-4ab3-8082-38da4f642de1","metricMeasures":[{"weight":1,"measure":0,"metricUuid":"0bafe0c2-a8f2-4c74-80c8-dbf3a5b8e9b7"}]},{"advice":null,"annotations":[],"createdAt":"2018-10-01T00:00:00Z","entityUuid":"e8b48f96-d3d5-4e54-a215-4454d08e6b59","eventType":"AddAnswerEvent","label":"Yes","uuid":"ca1e3a78-f3f1-4fd0-9734-11f7ddcbb04f","parentUuid":"4c7cd15f-90f9-4ab3-8082-38da4f642de1","metricMeasures":[{"weight":1,"measure":1,"metricUuid":"0bafe0c2-a8f2-4c74-80c8-dbf3a5b8e9b7"}]},{"annotations":[],"createdAt":"2018-10-01T00:00:00Z","text":"It is much easier to guarantee consistency and reproducibility if all data processing is done using automated work flows, especially if the workflow engine automatically keeps adequate provenance data.","entityUuid":"49199b05-73d7-4912-a5ca-bc1e14a09468","questionType":"OptionsQuestion","eventType":"AddQuestionEvent","title":"Will you make use of standard workflow engines and automatic work flows for all data analysis in the project?","requiredPhaseUuid":"1796fa3c-9f53-475f-89ff-c66a0453c42e","tagUuids":[],"uuid":"963b8744-0f37-4c81-af12-94a25b5c9476","parentUuid":"12a85bf3-1407-4783-9e73-564d75e7c98a"},{"annotations":[],"createdAt":"2018-10-01T00:00:00Z","entityUuid":"d522881a-9f3e-45fc-a420-f444e4da3ad0","eventType":"AddReferenceEvent","targetUuid":"28b10fd8-28a6-49b8-822d-f3d47780ab20","uuid":"cb6944f3-f8a6-4cea-bbbd-5f84dcdadb3e","parentUuid":"49199b05-73d7-4912-a5ca-bc1e14a09468","referenceType":"CrossReference","description":"Provenance as selection criterion for workflow engine"},{"advice":null,"annotations":[],"createdAt":"2018-10-01T00:00:00Z","entityUuid":"a9db9446-5bbc-431e-981d-d2f487ab28ae","eventType":"AddAnswerEvent","label":"No","uuid":"8306c3be-2e44-49a1-9cf4-6c6c838ce6fb","parentUuid":"49199b05-73d7-4912-a5ca-bc1e14a09468","metricMeasures":[{"weight":1,"measure":0,"metricUuid":"0bafe0c2-a8f2-4c74-80c8-dbf3a5b8e9b7"}]},{"advice":null,"annotations":[],"createdAt":"2018-10-01T00:00:00Z","entityUuid":"ea0ab328-184c-40f2-a391-c89617b37fe9","eventType":"AddAnswerEvent","label":"Yes","uuid":"a8baa5f1-5d26-487e-849e-cee79e6d46d3","parentUuid":"49199b05-73d7-4912-a5ca-bc1e14a09468","metricMeasures":[{"weight":1,"measure":1,"metricUuid":"0bafe0c2-a8f2-4c74-80c8-dbf3a5b8e9b7"}]},{"annotations":[],"createdAt":"2018-10-01T00:00:00Z","text":"Will you be able to find and reproduce exactly which version was used for any analysis? Not only for the major tools in the workflows, but also for all ''glue'' code and small tools you created especially for the project?","entityUuid":"56bc8ebb-aba5-4745-8034-17ed3fe4fe07","questionType":"OptionsQuestion","eventType":"AddQuestionEvent","title":"Are all software tools in the work flow professionally maintained, with version control?","requiredPhaseUuid":"1796fa3c-9f53-475f-89ff-c66a0453c42e","tagUuids":[],"uuid":"84d40a30-dd85-414d-b456-55e607025bd8","parentUuid":"12a85bf3-1407-4783-9e73-564d75e7c98a"},{"advice":null,"annotations":[],"createdAt":"2018-10-01T00:00:00Z","entityUuid":"76d2327b-8ac0-44eb-9d42-2434182824a0","eventType":"AddAnswerEvent","label":"No","uuid":"ccce25a5-3de9-4242-9c9f-bfe77791071b","parentUuid":"56bc8ebb-aba5-4745-8034-17ed3fe4fe07","metricMeasures":[{"weight":1,"measure":0,"metricUuid":"0bafe0c2-a8f2-4c74-80c8-dbf3a5b8e9b7"}]},{"advice":null,"annotations":[],"createdAt":"2018-10-01T00:00:00Z","entityUuid":"8afcd524-0916-4980-8bee-15b00bf5c335","eventType":"AddAnswerEvent","label":"Yes","uuid":"48fe8fab-d6dc-467a-b8ec-9bd8e9f6c46d","parentUuid":"56bc8ebb-aba5-4745-8034-17ed3fe4fe07","metricMeasures":[{"weight":1,"measure":1,"metricUuid":"0bafe0c2-a8f2-4c74-80c8-dbf3a5b8e9b7"}]},{"annotations":[],"createdAt":"2018-10-01T00:00:00Z","text":null,"entityUuid":"918d5fd1-ea37-468f-8acd-ca3e80203900","questionType":"OptionsQuestion","eventType":"AddQuestionEvent","title":"How will you validate the integrity of the results?","requiredPhaseUuid":"1796fa3c-9f53-475f-89ff-c66a0453c42e","tagUuids":[],"uuid":"73f7eb4b-7ba3-436c-b63d-327a18aa73a9","parentUuid":"10a10ffd-bfe1-4c6b-bbb6-3dfb1e63a5d5"},{"advice":null,"annotations":[],"createdAt":"2018-10-01T00:00:00Z","entityUuid":"30d1e85c-0e3e-482f-97f9-22a7658b329e","eventType":"AddAnswerEvent","label":"Explore","uuid":"3da0b0dc-1df8-46ef-9398-16111c27aa5a","parentUuid":"918d5fd1-ea37-468f-8acd-ca3e80203900","metricMeasures":[]},{"annotations":[],"createdAt":"2018-10-01T00:00:00Z","text":"There are surprisingly many complications that can cause (slight) inconsistencies between results when workflows are run on different compute infrastructures. A good way to make sure this does not bite you is to run a subset of all jobs on all different infrastructure to check the consistency.","entityUuid":"e8a08f27-9f82-4147-b446-822d34a5d468","questionType":"OptionsQuestion","eventType":"AddQuestionEvent","title":"Will you run a subset of your jobs several times across the different compute infrastructures you are using?","requiredPhaseUuid":"1796fa3c-9f53-475f-89ff-c66a0453c42e","tagUuids":[],"uuid":"94ae4ee2-cbb7-469d-9e8b-c09cdf868bc8","parentUuid":"30d1e85c-0e3e-482f-97f9-22a7658b329e"},{"advice":null,"annotations":[],"createdAt":"2018-10-01T00:00:00Z","entityUuid":"8d038086-a207-46f4-9e7c-180780d9c3a6","eventType":"AddAnswerEvent","label":"No","uuid":"723dd950-20d4-4a80-9d05-2105b5239855","parentUuid":"e8a08f27-9f82-4147-b446-822d34a5d468","metricMeasures":[{"weight":1,"measure":0,"metricUuid":"0bafe0c2-a8f2-4c74-80c8-dbf3a5b8e9b7"}]},{"advice":null,"annotations":[],"createdAt":"2018-10-01T00:00:00Z","entityUuid":"be0761b6-421a-4683-8ff9-de496868feea","eventType":"AddAnswerEvent","label":"Yes","uuid":"5d7b19e9-32cc-4125-b7e9-0c0657b27c4b","parentUuid":"e8a08f27-9f82-4147-b446-822d34a5d468","metricMeasures":[{"weight":1,"measure":1,"metricUuid":"0bafe0c2-a8f2-4c74-80c8-dbf3a5b8e9b7"}]},{"annotations":[],"createdAt":"2018-10-01T00:00:00Z","text":"Surrounding all tools in your data processing and analysis workflows with the ''boilerplate'' code necessary on the computer system you are using is tedious and error prone. Especially if you are using the same tools in multiple different work flows and/or on multiple different computer architectures. Automated instrumentation, e.g. by using a workflow management system, can prevent many mistakes.","entityUuid":"a3a4ce37-4ced-41df-8ec6-e42d87a6a3f1","questionType":"OptionsQuestion","eventType":"AddQuestionEvent","title":"Will you be instrumenting the tools into pipelines and workflows using automated tools?","requiredPhaseUuid":"1796fa3c-9f53-475f-89ff-c66a0453c42e","tagUuids":[],"uuid":"ac4c8e66-a70b-4c63-bf2b-a3a259e501ca","parentUuid":"30d1e85c-0e3e-482f-97f9-22a7658b329e"},{"advice":null,"annotations":[],"createdAt":"2018-10-01T00:00:00Z","entityUuid":"9ffbb7f2-5eb8-455a-bd98-6547887e0eb6","eventType":"AddAnswerEvent","label":"No","uuid":"24d697e9-b03b-4db5-8e2c-caacc1ce04ae","parentUuid":"a3a4ce37-4ced-41df-8ec6-e42d87a6a3f1","metricMeasures":[{"weight":1,"measure":0,"metricUuid":"0bafe0