### 1.0.1

* Fix: Adding forgotten question mark to end of question (39e0cc7c-17fe-4991-88d8-1280c3fe7923) in chapter 1 according to: [ds-km@644a373](https://github.com/ds-wizard/ds-km/commit/644a373685dc4ac15b76e86667a90151ca9c70ca)

### 1.0.0

* Initial version transformed from the previous DS-KM GitHub repository up to [ds-km@8442837](https://github.com/ds-wizard/ds-km/commit/8442837dbe3ff899b09e7d8d3fc1107e935a876f)', 'Apache-2.0', 'dsw:root:2.2.0', null, null, '[{"annotations":{"changed":false},"createdAt":"2020-11-11T10:49:19.845Z","text":{"value":"Before you decide to embark on any new study, it is good practice to check all options to re-use existing available data, either collected or generated by yourself in an earlier project, or data from others (Barend Mons calls this \"Other PEople''s Data And Services\" or OPEDAS). This can include reusable data that have been created for an earlier study, and also so-called \"reference data\" which is used by many projects.\n\nIt is not because we can generate massive amounts of data that we always need to do so. Creating data with public money is bringing with it the responsibility to treat those data well and (if potentially useful) make them available for re-use by others. And the circle is only complete if such data is actually re-used.","changed":true},"questionUuids":{"value":["efc80cc8-8318-4f8c-acb7-dc1c60e491c1"],"changed":true},"entityUuid":"82fd0cce-2b41-423f-92ad-636d0872045c","eventType":"EditChapterEvent","title":{"changed":false},"uuid":"6e0372d1-d20b-4a55-b278-8f6bf574517e","parentUuid":"6f6241d9-136c-4770-9d58-8a3f39607052"},{"advice":{"value":"It is possible that you have overlooked existing data! This question is not only about data sets that are similar to what you want to determine yourself, but also reference data or data that should be mined from the existing literature. Further, it is very likely that you will refer to related data, e.g. other databases where you usually \"quickly look something up\", but that could maybe be properly integrated, especially if you need to do such lookups multiple times.","changed":true},"annotations":{"changed":false},"createdAt":"2020-11-11T10:49:19.845Z","entityUuid":"72cdbc99-2707-4817-ac40-435a03e5e837","eventType":"EditAnswerEvent","followUpUuids":{"changed":false},"label":{"changed":false},"uuid":"66b4d227-7082-4bc7-9159-491c9bde1f61","parentUuid":"efc80cc8-8318-4f8c-acb7-dc1c60e491c1","metricMeasures":{"changed":false}},{"annotations":{"changed":false},"createdAt":"2020-11-11T10:49:19.845Z","text":{"value":"Many research fields have worked together to define what kind of metadata should really be collected when an experiment of a certain kind is performed and described. That information is described in a Minimal Metadata Standard. Often, these standards describe both what kind of information needs to be collected as well as the format in which it is expected.","changed":true},"entityUuid":"6226d7f2-565f-4991-94b3-c00be6aca20e","questionType":"OptionsQuestion","eventType":"EditQuestionEvent","title":{"changed":false},"requiredPhaseUuid":{"changed":false},"tagUuids":{"changed":false},"uuid":"97a747cb-0655-460d-830c-e311669cda8b","expertUuids":{"changed":false},"parentUuid":"6d18bfff-0f53-469b-934e-9806dda9d4fb","answerUuids":{"changed":false},"referenceUuids":{"changed":false}},{"annotations":{"changed":false},"createdAt":"2020-11-11T10:49:19.845Z","text":{"value":"Have you identified types of data that you will use that are used by others too? Some types of data (for example \"images\" or \"tables\") are used by many different projects. For such data, often common standards exist (in our example \"JPG\" and \"CSV\") that help to make these data reusable. Are you using such common data formats?\n\nPlease make sure you list all the data types that are important for your project. You should make sure also to list the formats used in any data sets that you are re-using.","changed":true},"entityUuid":"b08fe063-33f8-4380-b3a9-ba1e586dedf2","questionType":"ListQuestion","eventType":"EditQuestionEvent","itemTemplateQuestionUuids":{"changed":false},"title":{"changed":false},"requiredPhaseUuid":{"changed":false},"tagUuids":{"changed":false},"uuid":"cce5bd15-cccc-4036-b6dd-1f410c79ec23","expertUuids":{"changed":false},"parentUuid":"b1df3c74-0b1f-4574-81c4-4cc2d780c1af","referenceUuids":{"changed":false}},{"annotations":[],"createdAt":"2020-11-11T10:49:19.845Z","text":"Formats like XLS or SQL are very flexible; they can be adapted to many different uses, and this makes them good for interoperability. However, their flexibility also makes that it is not immediately obvious from the file structure how it can be used. The data needs a proper *description* in order for others (or yourself at a later time) to be able to unambiguously understand what it contains.","entityUuid":"192fc5d3-dc2a-495c-8f24-f59a4c5d95c9","questionType":"OptionsQuestion","eventType":"AddQuestionEvent","title":"Is this data format completely described?","requiredPhaseUuid":"1796fa3c-9f53-475f-89ff-c66a0453c42e","tagUuids":[],"uuid":"fa5c4f5e-6570-4b30-8ba6-1e66edd1434e","parentUuid":"b08fe063-33f8-4380-b3a9-ba1e586dedf2"},{"advice":"Plan time and budget for either documenting this data or for conversion to a well-described specific format.","annotations":[],"createdAt":"2020-11-11T10:49:19.845Z","entityUuid":"14503afc-3fe3-4e28-8f2d-81c065ee7565","eventType":"AddAnswerEvent","label":"No","uuid":"fba7bf6d-160c-4e1e-8629-2a944e0bb167","parentUuid":"192fc5d3-dc2a-495c-8f24-f59a4c5d95c9","metricMeasures":[]},{"advice":null,"annotations":[],"createdAt":"2020-11-11T10:49:19.845Z","entityUuid":"d75d94bb-6c3a-4170-a5a1-2a75a78629c2","eventType":"AddAnswerEvent","label":"Yes","uuid":"34d35098-d99d-47d5-b6cb-877e9249edfa","parentUuid":"192fc5d3-dc2a-495c-8f24-f59a4c5d95c9","metricMeasures":[]},{"annotations":{"changed":false},"createdAt":"2020-11-11T10:49:19.845Z","text":{"value":"Add each of the research project(s) that are you will be working on and for which the data and work are described in this DMP. Give each project a small identifying name for yourself.","changed":true},"entityUuid":"c3dabaaf-c946-4a0d-889c-ede966f97667","questionType":"ListQuestion","eventType"