### 1.0.2

* Fix: Adding some explanation to the list item questions (f5fef09d-ade5-4019-b089-f05bd89c34bc and b642c31d-a512-4ca7-8743-a2e0254006fa) in chapter 3 according to: [ds-km@96e28f4](https://github.com/ds-wizard/ds-km/commit/96e28f478d5dc6b59d384b5127f012dc2fe5f287)

### 1.0.1

* Fix: Adding forgotten question mark to end of question (39e0cc7c-17fe-4991-88d8-1280c3fe7923) in chapter 1 according to: [ds-km@644a373](https://github.com/ds-wizard/ds-km/commit/644a373685dc4ac15b76e86667a90151ca9c70ca)

### 1.0.0

* Initial version transformed from the previous DS-KM GitHub repository up to [ds-km@8442837](https://github.com/ds-wizard/ds-km/commit/8442837dbe3ff899b09e7d8d3fc1107e935a876f)', 'Apache-2.0', 'dsw:root:2.3.0', null, null, '[{"annotations":{"changed":false},"createdAt":"2021-11-02T10:22:46.775632Z","text":{"value":"We will make sure that we know what data will be coming together in the project, when it will be coming. We also need to make sure that we have adequate storage space to deal with it, and that all the responsibilities have been taken care of.\n\nSee also [Collecting in RDMKit](https://rdmkit.elixir-europe.org/collecting)","changed":true},"questionUuids":{"changed":false},"entityUuid":"b1df3c74-0b1f-4574-81c4-4cc2d780c1af","eventType":"EditChapterEvent","title":{"changed":false},"uuid":"d8e93d3f-741f-466e-b285-d1173d36bbf8","parentUuid":"6f6241d9-136c-4770-9d58-8a3f39607052"},{"annotations":{"changed":false},"createdAt":"2021-11-02T10:22:46.775632Z","text":{"value":"In this chapter we describe all the sources of data: they can e.g. come from instruments or from questionnaires; data can be newly collected as part of the current project, but it can also be pre-existing data that may need proper contracts with the maintainer, some pre-processing, and quality checks. It can also be reference data that is part of curated resources and (public) databases. \n\nFor more information see [Collecting in RDMKit](https://rdmkit.elixir-europe.org/collecting)","changed":true},"questionUuids":{"changed":false},"entityUuid":"b1df3c74-0b1f-4574-81c4-4cc2d780c1af","eventType":"EditChapterEvent","title":{"changed":false},"uuid":"bf8fde5e-e357-4722-9822-ef72a26e7216","parentUuid":"6f6241d9-136c-4770-9d58-8a3f39607052"},{"annotations":{"changed":false},"createdAt":"2021-11-02T10:22:46.775632Z","text":{"value":"Data analysis is normally done step-by-step.  It is important that for all data the origin and all processing and filtering steps are documented, otherwise results will not be reproducible. \n\nRe-users of the data also need this information to decide whether the data can be used for their purpose.","changed":true},"entityUuid":"948b5fd8-c1bd-457d-8f81-ea2fd093f541","questionType":"OptionsQuestion","eventType":"EditQuestionEvent","title":{"changed":false},"requiredPhaseUuid":{"changed":false},"tagUuids":{"changed":false},"uuid":"9c341560-a1cf-4e56-a600-813955ddcc02","expertUuids":{"changed":false},"parentUuid":"6d18bfff-0f53-469b-934e-9806dda9d4fb","answerUuids":{"changed":false},"referenceUuids":{"changed":false}},{"annotations":{"changed":false},"createdAt":"2021-11-02T10:22:46.775632Z","text":{"value":"For the re-usability of your data by yourself or others at a later stage, a lot of information about the data --for example how it was collected and how it can be used-- should be stored with the data. Such *data about the data* is called **metadata**, and this set of questions are about this metadata.","changed":true},"entityUuid":"8c962e6f-17ee-4b22-8ebb-9f06f779e3b3","questionType":"OptionsQuestion","eventType":"EditQuestionEvent","title":{"changed":false},"requiredPhaseUuid":{"changed":false},"tagUuids":{"changed":false},"uuid":"840c2fc4-9424-4ea3-a067-f7bd7861f512","expertUuids":{"changed":false},"parentUuid":"b1df3c74-0b1f-4574-81c4-4cc2d780c1af","answerUuids":{"changed":false},"referenceUuids":{"changed":false}},{"annotations":[],"createdAt":"2021-11-02T10:22:46.775632Z","text":"In the design of your experiment, there are many considerations and techniques that cab be used to ensure and monitor data quality.","entityUuid":"59cd7bb6-8b24-4a4b-9baa-e7147807c58d","questionType":"OptionsQuestion","eventType":"AddQuestionEvent","title":"What techniques are you using to ensure data quality?","requiredPhaseUuid":null,"tagUuids":[],"uuid":"1b8e9ffe-fefe-4cd0-b3bd-99f7955e2bc1","parentUuid":"b1df3c74-0b1f-4574-81c4-4cc2d780c1af"},{"advice":null,"annotations":[],"createdAt":"2021-11-02T10:22:46.775632Z","entityUuid":"f55f2b65-40ea-428c-99e3-f78b9e8032a0","eventType":"AddAnswerEvent","label":"Explore","uuid":"3b5b3804-fee0-413c-809f-5805b6906075","parentUuid":"59cd7bb6-8b24-4a4b-9baa-e7147807c58d","metricMeasures":[]},{"annotations":[],"createdAt":"2021-11-02T10:22:46.775632Z","text":null,"entityUuid":"9a4050de-5264-4de6-933c-3cfff3684119","questionType":"OptionsQuestion","eventType":"AddQuestionEvent","title":"Will you be repeating experiments to monitor consistency of the results?","requiredPhaseUuid":null,"tagUuids":[],"uuid":"539a33ca-d8c5-4a88-a7c1-ee9ce93e138c","parentUuid":"f55f2b65-40ea-428c-99e3-f78b9e8032a0"},{"advice":null,"annotations":[],"createdAt":"2021-11-02T10:22:46.775632Z","entityUuid":"33e6d62f-a1a8-4cee-ad93-dea427405722","eventType":"AddAnswerEvent","label":"No","uuid":"2b83b4d6-4f6f-49cb-90c1-185e57442174","parentUuid":"9a4050de-5264-4de6-933c-3cfff3684119","metricMeasures":[]},{"advice":null,"annotations":[],"createdAt":"2021-11-02T10:22:46.775632Z","entityUuid":"faad6703-7c7a-43e7-9b38-33ea5fed66c2","eventType":"AddAnswerEvent","label":"Yes","uuid":"70610b9c-a94a-4cfe-989d-9be4876ab7c7","parentUuid":"9a4050de-5264-4de6-933c-3cfff3684119","metricMeasures":[]},{"annotations":[],"createdAt":"2021-11-02T10:22:46.775632Z","text":null,"entityUuid":"691f896d-c28f-4da8-b648-9dab7066d454","questionType":"OptionsQuestion","eventType":"AddQuestionEvent","title":"Will you include experiments for which the outcome is known to monitor consistency of the results?","requiredPhaseUuid":null,"tagUuids":[],"uuid":"baf34381-6384-4ea7-aa8c-d4d746612809","parentUuid":"f55f2b65-40ea-428c-99e3-f78b9e8032a0"},{"advice":null,"annotations":[],"createdAt":"2021-11-02T10:22:46.775632Z","entityUuid":"40f366d2-57b8-4113-b597-ad2fd2376c0c","eventType":"AddAnswerEvent","label":"No","uuid":"7b25e7b7-8914-4426-a18e-7ac4a61aba7b","parentUuid":"691f896d-c28f-4da8-b648-9dab7066d454","metricMeasures":[]},{"advice":null,"annotations":[],"createdAt":"2021-11-02T10:22:46.775632Z","entityUuid":"d791892c-efe1-48b0-bb5f-86660c0fabed","eventType":"AddAnswerEvent","label":"Yes","uuid":"246dd1ba-7299-4fc5-ba2e-e27e17d03059","parentUuid":"691f896d-c28f-4da8-b648-9dab7066d454","metricMeasures":[]},{"annotations":[],"createdAt":"2021-11-02T10:22:46.775632Z","text":null,"entityUuid":"aec4bc32-9a52-4903-a17d-cb8d69bb8417","questionType":"OptionsQuestion","eventType":"AddQuestionEvent","title":"Are you using any other techniques to monitor data quality?","requiredPhaseUuid":null,"tagUuids":[],"uuid":"2ac189f4-c0f0-426a-b9da-4cdd27ca320c","parentUuid":"f55f2b65-40ea-428c-99e3-f78b9e8032a0"},{"advice":null,"annotations":[],"createdAt":"2021-11-02T10:22:46.775632Z","entityUuid":"0f714535-c6a3-4697-a3e4-525bfded85f7","eventType":"AddAnswerEvent","label":"No","uuid":"28817ae5-9a82-4c03-a9c1-2f850c1b17fd","parentUuid":"aec4bc32-9a52-4903-a17d-cb8d69bb8417","metricMeasures":[]},{"advice":null,"annotations":[],"createdAt":"2021-11-02T10:22:46.775632Z","entityUuid":"faa94ef2-24b4-435c-9a5d-972ee698e157","eventType":"AddAnswerEvent","label":"Yes","uuid":"9b381d4b-afa9-4060-95ae-f61eb0399891","parentUuid":"aec4bc32-9a52-4903-a17d-cb8d69bb8417","metricMeasures":[]},{"annotations":[],"createdAt":"2021-11-02T10:22:46.775632Z","text":null,"entityUuid":"51e61d30-3837-4ab5-b5e5-7a832d456d63","questionType":"ValueQuestion","eventType":"AddQuestionEvent","title":"What other techniques do you use to monitor data quality?","requiredPhaseUuid":null,"tagUuids":[],"uuid":"b86ecdde-daf2-4419-879a-eb9dd121315e","parentUuid":"faa94ef2-24b4-435c-9a5d-972ee698e157","valueType":"TextQuestionValueType"},{"advice":{"changed":false},"annotations":{"changed":false},"createdAt":"2021-11-02T10:22:46.775632Z","entityUuid":"0fd3cd1c-e0e8-41d5-9beb-3f1faba0fb91","eventType":"EditAnswerEvent","followUpUuids":{"changed":false},"label":{"value":"The ownership for the data is arranged in another way","changed":true},"uuid":"7d32397e-8b48-4079-ba1e-98e4efc8c611","parentUuid":"cb7d17a8-30c0-489d-a43c-702b27d97611","metricMeasures":{"changed":false}},{"annotations":[],"createdAt":"2021-11-02T10:22:46.775632Z","text":"Very many kinds of data are connected to people. If there could be a way for someone, including yourself, to find out who that person is, that is considered personal data.\n\nSimple examples are name, birth day or address; but there are many other data that can be personal: for example a combination of a location and a time, genetic information, or an X-ray of the skull.","entityUuid":"49c009cb-a38c-4836-9780-8a8b3dd1cbac","questionType":"OptionsQuestion","eventType":"AddQuestionEvent","title":"Will you collect any data connected to a person, \"personal data\"?","requiredPhaseUuid":null,"tagUuids":[],"uuid":"4e64fff0-1177-4d76-8421-963720fae346","parentUuid":"b1df3c74-0b1f-4574-81c4-4cc2d780c1af"},{"advice":null,"annotations":[],"createdAt":"2021-11-02T10:22:46.775632Z","entityUuid":"4bdc319d-282a-4a80-9cdd-78d2081e812b","eventType":"AddAnswerEvent","label":"No","uuid":"2eda9560-888d-430e-a492-8730ec2bd920","parentUuid":"49c009cb-a38c-4836-9780-8a8b3dd1cbac","metricMeasures":[]},{"advice":null,"annotations":[],"createdAt":"2021-11-02T10:22:46.775632Z","entityUuid":"421e2d3e-c95c-4244-9465-de8f1cb8aeba","eventType":"AddAnswerEvent","label":"Yes","uuid":"3153bef8-52a4-4b23-bf16-0e5750dc9dc1","parentUuid":"49c009cb-a38c-4836-9780-8a8b3dd1cbac","metricMeasures":[]},{"annotations":{"changed":false},"createdAt":"2021-11-02T10:22:46.775632Z","text":{"changed":false},"questionUuids":{"value":["b08fe063-33f8-4380-b3a9-ba1e586dedf2","2bac9020-99cf-4463-8d34-0b0eb2781cd1","5ba53879-eb48-47f2-a73b-f7f7d83bf030","8c962e6f-17ee-4b22-8ebb-9f06f779e3b3","f87c331d-794a-42c8-a910-61a2a9110dab","f038bd46-ee4e-4f53-b7ea-482381c2c855","ab4b3f39-dfab-45a5-9489-2d46ceacbb73","0e810343-6026-4992-8ea0-5539cbc77093","49c009cb-a38c-4836-9780-8a8b3dd1cbac","f5e162ee-1077-4ebe-a932-192bc7f67e98","cb7d17a8-30c0-489d-a43c-702b27d97611","59cd7bb6-8b24-4a4b-9baa-e7147807c58d"],"changed":true},"entityUuid":"b1df3c74-0b1f-4574-81c4-4cc2d780c1af","eventType":"EditChapterEvent","title":{"changed":false},"uuid":"151cf109-fb1c-405b-b2c2-44f7e59a40a5","parentUuid":"6f6241d9-136c-4770-9d58-8a3f39607052"},{"annotations":[],"createdAt":"2021-11-02T10:22:46.775632Z","text":"Many countries, including the European Union, have strict laws that require anyone who processes personal data to do so only with a good reason. The allowed \"good reasons\" are called \"legal base\" for the processing of the data.","entityUuid":"be4651c9-9a8c-4e10-a158-61b94ca0e139","questionType":"OptionsQuestion","eventType":"AddQuestionEvent","title":"What legal basis are you using to collect and process the personal data?","requiredPhaseUuid":null,"tagUuids":[],"uuid":"52d0f3ff-63b8-4077-8e44-bd20c72e5c31","parentUuid":"421e2d3e-c95c-4244-9465-de8f1cb8aeba"},{"advice":null,"annotations":[],"createdAt":"2021-11-02T10:22:46.775632Z","entityUuid":"73cd2dda-41ba-456b-9a4e-aa34c78f2fcf","eventType":"AddAnswerEvent","label":"We ask the data subjects for their consent","uuid":"4af8fab5-5602-4b3d-9855-56d235557511","parentUuid":"be4651c9-9a8c-4e10-a158-61b94ca0e139","metricMeasures":[]},{"advice":null,"annotations":[],"createdAt":"2021-11-02T10:22:46.775632Z","entityUuid":"1dfe0a6d-4281-4d5e-bcaa-5e20fa28a591","eventType":"AddAnswerEvent","label":"We require the processing to fulfil our contract with the data subjects","uuid":"6ef53ca2-5a54-4a51-8382-913704489a7b","parentUuid":"be4651c9-9a8c-4e10-a158-61b94ca0e139","metricMeasures":[]},{"advice":null,"annotations":[],"createdAt":"2021-11-02T10:22:46.775632Z","entityUuid":"9d5e3104-2b6b-4d95-848e-253ef069d8b3","eventType":"AddAnswerEvent","label":"We have a legitimate interest: data subjects all expect us to do this data processing because of who we are","uuid":"ede368d4-1dbe-49fa-a2cd-957daf8773ba","parentUuid":"be4651c9-9a8c-4e10-a158-61b94ca0e139","metricMeasures":[]},{"advice":null,"annotations":[],"createdAt":"2021-11-02T10:22:46.775632Z","entityUuid":"557a5401-a94a-4a37-af2e-a21829557bfa","eventType":"AddAnswerEvent","label":"Vital interest: we need to do this to save the data subject","uuid":"47712b38-767f-49d8-9ea4-01ba2969f8e5","parentUuid":"be4651c9-9a8c-4e10-a158-61b94ca0e139","metricMeasures":[]},{"advice":null,"annotations":[],"createdAt":"2021-11-02T10:22:46.775632Z","entityUuid":"f10de3a8-2751-42c7-afaa-92eed4833f8e","eventType":"AddAnswerEvent","label":"Legal requirement: We are legally obliged to do this data processing","uuid":"3e82cdfd-e0c3-458f-8737-506daf37d709","parentUuid":"be4651c9-9a8c-4e10-a158-61b94ca0e139","metricMeasures":[]},{"advice":"Note that scientific research is not considered public interest in many jurisdictions.","annotations":[],"createdAt":"2021-11-02T10:22:46.775632Z","entityUuid":"c732f0b9-2f66-47f4-902f-724a44cdfd4b","eventType":"AddAnswerEvent","label":"Public interest: We do this for the benefit of society, and this is more important than the privacy of the subjects","uuid":"bbe002a2-fb73-4039-89cf-8e2311e6ef29","parentUuid":"be4651c9-9a8c-4e10-a158-61b94ca0e139","metricMeasures":[]},{"advice":{"value":"Note that consent needs to be completely voluntary. If the subject gets any service or good in return for their permission, this is not considered consent. Also note that in European (GDPR) law, a data subject should be able to retract their consent at any moment.","changed":true},"annotations":{"changed":false},"createdAt":"2021-11-02T10:22:46.775632Z","entityUuid":"73cd2dda-41ba-456b-9a4e-aa34c78f2fcf","eventType":"EditAnswerEvent","followUpUuids":{"changed":false},"label":{"changed":false},"uuid":"8cb76056-d197-48cd-a3bc-3c80250b205a","parentUuid":"be4651c9-9a8c-4e10-a158-61b94ca0e139","metricMeasures":{"changed":false}},{"createdAt":"2021-11-02T10:22:46.775632Z","entityUuid":"f5e162ee-1077-4ebe-a932-192bc7f67e98","eventType":"MoveQuestionEvent","targetUuid":"73cd2dda-41ba-456b-9a4e-aa34c78f2fcf","uuid":"ccf6eafa-4ecf-408a-b524-60db0b7a007c","parentUuid":"b1df3c74-0b1f-4574-81c4-